      • onException

        void onException(Request<ReturnType,SOAP11Fault> request,
               SOAPException e)
        Called if the running SOAP request hits an exception during execution. Note that this uses SOAP11Faults by default - if you need to consume SOAP 1.2 Faults, or need to parse extra details of the SOAP Fault, please use SOAPObserver directly.
        Specified by:
        onException in interface SOAPObserver<ReturnType,SOAP11Fault>
        Parameters:
        request - The Request instance that has encountered an exception.
        e - The exception that's been encountered.
